\begin{align*}
(\frac{d1}{2})^2 + (\frac{d2}{2})^2 &= (\sqrt{89})^2 \\
(\frac{d1}{2})^2 + (\frac{d1 + 6}{2})^2 &= 89 \\
\frac{d1^2}{4} + \frac{d1^2 + 12d1 + 36}{4} &= 89 \\
d1^2 + d1^2 + 12d1 + 36 &= 356 \\
2d1^2 + 12d1 - 320 &= 0 \\
d1^2 + 6d1 - 160 &= 0 \\
(d1 + 16)(d1 - 10) &= 0
\end{align*}
Since d1 must be positive, we have d1 = 10 units and d2 = 16 units. Therefore, the area of the rhombus is:</>
\begin{align*}
A &= 1/2 * d1 * d2 \\
&= 1/2 * 10 * 16 \\
&= 80 \text{ square units}
\end{align*}

